<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1152,762,1089]" box="[151,1152,762,788]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">The group comprises 2 species. It is characterised by the following 7 character states:</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1152,762,1089]" box="[151,410,805,831]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">- costa straight;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1152,762,1089]" box="[151,499,848,874]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">- ampulla very narrow;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1152,762,1089]" box="[151,752,891,917]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">- ampulla with small ventral process at base;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1152,762,1089]" box="[151,619,934,960]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">- ampulla without a dorsal hump;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1152,762,1089]" box="[151,466,977,1003]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">- editum finger-like;</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1152,762,1089]" box="[151,713,1020,1046]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">- phallus extremely long and narrow; and</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1152,762,1089]" box="[151,671,1063,1089]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">- antrum with prominent basal pouch.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
